The President and First Lady will be traveling to Maui on August 21 to meet with first responders, survivors, and officials in the aftermath of the deadly wildfires on the island. They will witness the impacts of the fires and discuss the next steps in the recovery effort. President Biden has been coordinating with FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell, Hawaii Senators Mazie Hirono and Brian Schatz, and Governor Josh Green to ensure federal support for Hawaii's recovery. The visit is scheduled for when the search and recovery efforts are expected to be at a stage that allows for a presidential visit.